-- Mellanox Rallies to Record, Closing Gap With U.S.-Traded Shares
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-07-04T07:38:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/mellanox-rallies-to-record-closing-gap-with-u-s-traded-shares.html
Mellanox Technologies Ltd. (MLNX) , an
Israeli developer of technology used to transfer and store data,
rose to a record, closing the gap with the U.S.-traded shares.  The  shares  gained 3.5 percent to 297.2 shekels, or the
equivalent of $75.75, at 10:35 a.m. in  Tel Aviv , the highest
intraday level since July 2007 when the shares were listed in
Israel. The New York-traded stock advanced 3.7 percent to $75.02
yesterday.  Harel Finance Trade Securities Ltd. yesterday raised the
price estimate to $80 from $58 a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
